docs.abstract: Lawmakers and others criticized the social network after a New York Times report revealed Facebook gave its partners extensive access to user data.
docs.snippet: Lawmakers and others criticized the social network after a New York Times report revealed Facebook gave its partners extensive access to user data.
docs.lead_paragraph: Facebook and some of the other largest technology firms in the world faced sharp criticism on Wednesday for failing to disclose the extent of the social network’s data-sharing deals, many of which went back to the company’s early years.

headline.main: Facebook Rebuked for Failing to Disclose Data-Sharing Deals
headline.print_headline: Facebook  Criticized For Betraying Users’ Data

byline.original: By Michael LaForgia, Nicholas Confessore and Gabriel J.X. Dance

docs.abstract: Seventeen companies that make apps designed to fight iPhone addiction called on Apple to let them use technology that would resolve privacy concerns.
docs.snippet: Seventeen companies that make apps designed to fight iPhone addiction called on Apple to let them use technology that would resolve privacy concerns.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Last year, Apple announced that it had created tools to help people limit the time they and their children spent on their iPhones. Around the same time, Apple began purging from its App Store a number of apps that offered similar services.

headline.main: Apps Purged by Apple Say It Holds the Key They Need to Get Back In
headline.print_headline: Apps Purged by Apple Say They Have Answer to Privacy Concerns

docs.abstract: The company’s move to shift assembly of the only major product it had made in America outside the country comes amid a continuing trade war between the United States and China.
docs.snippet: The company’s move to shift assembly of the only major product it had made in America outside the country comes amid a continuing trade war between the United States and China.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Apple will manufacture a new version of its Mac Pro computer in China, shifting production of the only major product the company has assembled in the United States outside the country, a person familiar with the plans said on Friday.

headline.main: Apple to Manufacture New Mac Pro Computer in China Instead of U.S.
headline.print_headline: Apple to Manufacture New Mac Pro in China

docs.abstract: This year the smartwatch is expected to outsell the entire Swiss industry. And who knows what could happen when health apps are fully developed.
docs.snippet: This year the smartwatch is expected to outsell the entire Swiss industry. And who knows what could happen when health apps are fully developed.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Apple’s chief executive, Timothy D. Cook, announced the Apple Watch in September 2014, the Swiss watch industry shuddered.

headline.main: Apple Watch Hasn’t Crushed the Swiss. Not Yet.

docs.abstract: An investigation by The New York Times revealed how Facebook fought back against critics during a flood of crises — with delays, denials and an influence campaign in Washington.
docs.snippet: An investigation by The New York Times revealed how Facebook fought back against critics during a flood of crises — with delays, denials and an influence campaign in Washington.
docs.lead_paragraph: For more than a year, Facebook has endured cascading crises — over Russian misinformation, data privacy and abusive content — that transformed the Silicon Valley icon into an embattled giant accused of corporate overreach and negligence.

headline.main: Damage Control at Facebook: 6 Takeaways From The Times’s Investigation

docs.abstract: A federal grand jury is looking at partnerships that gave major tech companies broad access to Facebook users’ information.
docs.snippet: A federal grand jury is looking at partnerships that gave major tech companies broad access to Facebook users’ information.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors are conducting a criminal investigation into data deals Facebook struck with some of the world’s largest technology companies, intensifying scrutiny of the social media giant’s business practices as it seeks to rebound from a year of scandal and setbacks.

headline.main: Facebook’s Data Deals Are Under Criminal Investigation
headline.print_headline: Criminal Investigation Digs Into Facebook’s Data-Sharing Deals

docs.abstract: The international tax system is behind the times. But we need coordinated reform.
docs.snippet: The international tax system is behind the times. But we need coordinated reform.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last Thursday, the French Senate passed a digital services tax, which would impose an entirely new tax on large multinationals that provide digital services to consumers or users in France.

headline.main: Beware. Other Nations Will Follow France With Their Own Digital Tax.
headline.print_headline: Digital Services Will Be Taxed, but How?

docs.abstract: A wide range of companies are lining up to complain about Silicon Valley’s power as lawmakers and regulators step up their scrutiny of Big Tech.
docs.snippet: A wide range of companies are lining up to complain about Silicon Valley’s power as lawmakers and regulators step up their scrutiny of Big Tech.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Oracle and the Handpulled Noodle would seem to have little in common. One is a multibillion-dollar software company in Silicon Valley with tens of thousands of employees all over the world. The other is a small Harlem spot that serves Chinese comfort food and is known for its tasty dumplings.

headline.main: Anger at Big Tech Unites Noodle Pullers and Code Writers
headline.print_headline: Smaller Rivals  Aim Slingshots At Tech Giants
